    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-31T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-31T01:00:00-05:00" n="361"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.506/47: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-31T13:00:00+07:00"
                            >July 31, 1943—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 20—5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–21. Department’s telegram no. 889, July 12, 5 p.m.</p>
                <p>Responsible official Finance Ministry states insurance project still vague.
                    Proposal jointly drawn up by Office of Four Government Banks and Central Trust
                    is for company with CN $60 million capital to take over insurance department of
                    Central Trust and possibly other insurance companies in which Government has an
                    interest. Proposed company would handle war risk insurance and might be given
                    monopoly of reinsurance on Government property but would not handle reinsurance
                    on private property. Capital would be subscribed by Central Trust and Government
                    banks with possibly some national treasury participation. American participation
                    not suggested <pb facs="0449" n="439" xml:id="pg_439"/> and seems most unlikely.
                    Impossible to say yet whether project will materialize or in what form.</p>
                <p>Officers of local insurance companies suspect project is one for monopoly of all
                    reinsurance, though they have no information as to details.</p>
                <p>Project was reported in May political report,<note n="49" xml:id="d361fn49"
                        >Despatch No. 1255, June 12, not printed.</note> economic section,
                    sub-section 1–<hi rend="italic">b</hi>–4, 2d paragraph. Department will be kept
                    informed of developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
